      "content": "# present document model proposals to user before implementing\n\nBefore creating any document model, present the full proposal:\n- State schema (global and local if applicable)\n- Modules and their operations\n- Error types for each operation\n- Any architectural decisions (scope choices, object relationships)\n\nWait for explicit user approval before implementing. This prevents wasted work on wrong assumptions and gives the user a chance to refine the design.\n\nSince [[one operation per user intent keeps concerns separated]], the proposal should show how each user action maps to a specific operation.\n\n---\n\nTopics:\n- [[mcp workflows]]",
